'''Mitch Maddox''' is a computer systems manager and former [[Internet personality]]. In a promotion for several Internet companies, he changed his name to '''DotComGuy''' and lived the entire year of 2000 in his house in [[Dallas]], [[Texas]], buying all food and other necessities online. Video from the house was streamed on the dotcomguy.com web site.<ref name="CouldryMcCarthy2004">{{cite book|last1=Couldry|first1=Nick|last2=McCarthy|first2=Anna|title=MediaSpace: place, scale, and culture in a media age|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F6QrJwlOnQsC&pg=PA200|accessdate=31 March 2011|date=2004-01-07|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-415-29175-0|page=200}}</ref> Sponsors of the project included [[United Parcel Service]], [[3Com]], [[Network Solutions]], [[Piper Jaffray]], [[Travelocity]] and an online grocer (now called Edwardo's). The site has since been acquired and today offers an on-site technical assistance service. <ref>{{cite web|title=Richfield resident helps create DotComGuy|url=https://www.hometownsource.com/sun_current/richfield-resident-helps-create-dotcomguy-for-location-based-tech-services/article_28fd142c-ce19-11e7-94d4-ef8e3b0fad07.html|accessdate=4 January 2018|deadurl=no}}</ref>
Maddox is now a [[technology evangelist]] for [[Ultimate Software]].<ref>{{cite web|title=FEI Portland Chapter Newsletter|url=http://www-new-726.ultimatesoftware.com/HR-Workshop-Speakers/70132000000pqoD/147|accessdate=30 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150430144930/http://www-new-726.ultimatesoftware.com/HR-Workshop-Speakers/70132000000pqoD/147|archivedate=30 April 2015|df=}}</ref> At the end of each year he holds a day-long DotComGuy reunion on [[Internet relay chat]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DotComGuy Fan Chat Reunion|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X9G-hbyBf1w|accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref>
