{{one source|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Keskilaakso | logo = | image = | caption = | type = Newspaper | format = | owners = | founder = | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = Stiina Kokkonen | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | foundation = {{start date and age|1931}} (Kymen Keskilaakso) | political = | language = [[Finnish language|Finnish]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = | circulation = 4,651 (2013) | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = [http://www.keskilaakso.fi/ ''Keskilaakso''] }}
'''''Keskilaakso''''' is a newspaper published typically tuesdays and thursdays in [[Kouvola]], [[Finland]].<ref>Keskilaakso, August 27</ref>
==History== ''Keskilaakso'' was established 1931 with a name ''Kymen Keskilaakso''. First publishing in November 1931, at that time, editor-in-chief was F. A. Havola. 1975 name became to be ''Anjalankosken Sanomat'' and at 2007 newspaper was named to Keskilaakso.
